  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [ ] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (a152664 2022-05-04T17:45:52.953502+00:00)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (M1)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nWith the following structure:\r\n\r\n```\r\n.\r\n├── foundry.toml\r\n├── lib\r\n│   ├── dep\r\n│   │   ├── foundry.toml\r\n│   │   ├── src\r\n│   │   │   └── dep.sol\r\n├── src\r\n│   └── try2.sol\r\n```\r\n\r\nRunning `forge config` gives:\r\n```\r\n# (...)\r\nremappings = [\r\n    'dep/=lib/dep/src/',\r\n    'ds-test/=lib/forge-std/lib/ds-test/src/',\r\n    'forge-std/=lib/forge-std/src/',\r\n]\r\n```\r\n\r\nHowever, if in `./lib/dep/foundry.toml` I replace `src = 'src'` with `src = 'src2'`, running `forge config` gives:\r\n```\r\n# (...)\r\nremappings = [\r\n    'dep/=lib/dep/src/',\r\n    'ds-test/=lib/forge-std/lib/ds-test/src/',\r\n    'forge-std/=lib/forge-std/src/',\r\n    'src2/=lib/dep/src2/',\r\n]\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhich means that I cannot use `import \"dep/dep.sol\";`",
